Voce Capital Management, LLC Key Developments

Voce Capital Presses Rudolph Technologies, Nanometrics to Merge
Jan 19 17
Voce Capital Management, LLC is pressing Nanometrics Incorporated (NasdaqGS:NANO) and Rudolph Technologies, Inc. (NYSE:RTEC) to merge, saying the two would be stronger together. In a letter to investors on January 19, 2017, Voce Capital Management LLC said a combination of Rudolph and Nanometrics would lead to cost-cutting and revenue growth through cross-selling to each other’s customers. Voce Capital Management owns about 1% of each company. The two companies have been in talks about a deal, according to people familiar with the matter, but it isn’t clear where they currently stand.


Voce Capital Management, LLC Presents at 7th Annual Shareholder Activism Conference, Nov-03-2016
Nov 3 16
Voce Capital Management, LLC Presents at 7th Annual Shareholder Activism Conference, Nov-03-2016 . Venue: New York, New York, United States. Speakers: J. Daniel Plants, Managing Partner, Founder, and Chief Investment Officer.


Voce Capital Management Announces Management Changes
Jan 26 16
Voce Capital Management LLC announced the addition of two industry veterans to its executive team. Both hires are timely as Voce continues to capitalize on the
Firm’s successful five-year track record. Mark Shamia has joined as Chief Operating Officer and Chief Financial Officer. Mr. Shamia is a veteran of the asset management industry and brings over 20 years of experience in similar roles with other alternative investment managers. Additionally, Nicholas Heldfond has joined as Head of Business Development and Investor Relations. Mr. Heldfond brings over 15 years of marketing and investor relations experience in the asset management industry. Mr. Heldfond will initiate a formal marketing program to drive the Firm’s ongoing growth.


